Privacy Policy
Effective date: Dec 12, 2024

This Privacy Policy explains what personal data is collected when you (you or User) use the Be-Pass website and/or mobile application (We) and the services provided through it (together the “Service”), and how this personal data will be used and shared.
Please read the Privacy Policy carefully before using our Service.  We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time and in this case, we will notify you about it. Our Terms of Service are available here https://www.be-pass.com/termsofservice/.
BY USING THE SERVICE, YOU AGREE AND ASSERT YOU HAVE READ, UNDERSTAND, AND AGREE TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY YOU ASSERT YOU ARE OF LEGAL AGE (18 YEARS OLD)
If you disagree with these assertions and promises, you must (a) delete your account using the functionality found in “Settings” in the Be-Pass, or contact us and request deletion of your data; (b) cancel any subscriptions using the functionality provided by Apple (if you are using iOS) or Google (if you are using Android); and (c) delete the Be-Pass from your devices.
 
Definitions:
“Personally identifiable information” any data that could potentially be used to identify a particular person.
“GDPR” the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data.
“EEA” includes all current member states to the European Union and the European Economic Area.
“Process”, in respect of personal data, includes to collection, storage, and disclose to third parties.
1.                   CATEGORIES OF PERSONAL DATA COLLECTED
1.1.               DATA PROVIDED BY USER
When the User registers for and/or use the Service User provide Be-Pass with full name, age, physical data, sensitive data, personal data, connection data, and-mail.
When the User uses Services, the Be-Pass may collect User’s information, connection, location, full address, profession, images, phone number.
1.2.             Data provided by third parties
When the User decides to log in using a third party service similar to (Google) Be-Pass gets personal data from respective User’s account. This includes User’s age and name. Unless User choses to opt out on the login screen, Be-Pass will also collect other data, such as email address. For more information, please refer to the policies of third party services chosen for log in.
1.3.             Data collected automatically:
1.3.1.        Reference data
Be-Pass collect data about User’s referring to Be-Pass or URL. It may be the app or place on the Web where User were when were tapped on Be-Pass advertisement.
1.3.2.       Advertising ID’s
Be-Pass collects User’s Apple Identifier for advertising (“IDFA”) or Google Advertising ID (“AAID”) (depending on the operating system of User’s device). User can typically reset these numbers through the settings of User’s device’s operating system (but Be-Pass does not control this).
1.3.3.      Device and Location data.
Be-Pass collects data from User’s mobile device. Examples of such data include: device settings, model of a device, hardware ID, operating system, language settings, IP address, time zone, Internet service provider, mobile carrier, Google ID.
1.3.4.      Usage data
Be-Pass records how the User interacts with the Service. For example, Be-Pass logs User’s taps on certain areas of the interface, features, and content the User interacts with, how often User use the Be-Pass. User’s searching, texts the User write, the time and duration of User’s using the platform, how long User is in the Be-Pass and User’s subscription orders. Be-Pass also record the advertising in Be-Pass with which User interact (and links to which those advertising lead).
1.3.5.      Location Information.
If the User has enabled location services on mobile device, Be-Pass collects location information to calculate quantity of steps in a day, running length, and reading the miles with voice. User can disable location services on their phone.
2.                  PURPOSES FOR COLLECTION OF PERSONALLY IDENTIFIABLE DATA
2.1.             Provision of Service
Be-Pass collects personally identifiable data to provide service to its User’s. It includes enabling the User to use the Service in a seamless manner and preventing or addressing service errors or technical issues.
2.2.            Communication regarding use of Service
Be-Pass may communicate with User’s by push notifications or e-mails. Such communicating may include motivational messages and reminders encouraging the User to follow his card and feedbacks, or other information about the Be-Pass. Users may receive a push notification every day at a particular time reminding to make some actions. User may also opt out of receiving push notifications by changing the settings on the mobile device.
Be-Pass may collect data concerning the date and time when the message was viewed by User, as well as when User interacted with it, such as by clicking on links included in the message.
2.3.            Customization of User’s experience
Be-Pass processes User’s personally through identifiable data, such as services and prices, to adjust the content of the Service and make offers tailored to User’s personal preferences. Due to such processing.
2.4.           Management of accounts and provision of customer support
Be-Pass processes User’s personally identifiable data to respond to User’s requests for technical support, service information or to any other communication the user initiates. This includes accessing User’s account to address technical support requests. Be-Pass may send User notifications or emails about the performance of Service, security, payment transactions, notices regarding Terms of Service or this Privacy Policy.
2.5.           Sending of marketing communications
Be-Pass processes User’s personally identifiable data for marketing purposes. The User may receive information about products, such as for example, special offers.
Be-Pass may also show advertisements and send push notifications for marketing purposes. To opt out of receiving push notifications, User need to change the settings on device.
2.6.           Personalization of marketing
Be-Pass use User’s personally identifiable data to tailor advertising and possibly show them to User at the relevant time.
User may opt out or influence personalized advertising by editing following settings.
iOS: Go to “Settings,” then “Privacy” and tap “Advertising” to select “Limit Ad Track”. Also User can reset advertising identifier in the same section.
Android: Open the Google Settings, tap “Ads” and enable “opt out of interest-based ads”. User can reset advertising identifier in the same section.
Google Ads is an advertisings delivery service provided by Google. It allows Be-Pass to tailor the way the advertisements appear. For example, show an advertisement to users who have purchased a subscription. Some other examples of events that may be used for tailoring advertisings includes, installing Be-Pass, finishing a training session or training program. Google allows its users to opt out of Google’s personalized ads and to prevent their data from being used by Google Analytics.
2.7.            To enforce our Terms of Service and to prevent and combat fraud
Be-Pass uses personal data to enforce agreements and contractual commitments, to detect, prevent, and combat fraud. Be-Pass may share User’s information with others, including law enforcement agencies (in particular, if a dispute arises in connection with Terms of Use).
2.8.           Researching and analyzing of use of the Service
Be-Pass performs researching and analyzing to, maintain, improve, innovate, plan, design, analyze operations, and modernize Be-Pass. This data is also used to test and improve offers, for statistical analysis purposes. It allows to better understand what features and training plans of Users like more, what categories of Users use Be-Pass.
Be-Pass uses Google Analytics to help analyze how Users use it. Google Analytics for mobile apps provides a platform to measure User interactions. This tool allows Be-Pass to better understand and optimize User’s engagement with application.
Be-Pass uses Fabric, which is an analytics service provided by Crashlytics, a business division of Google.
 
 
 
2.9.           To comply with legal obligations
Be-Pass may process, use, or share User’s data when the law requires it, in particular, if a law enforcement agency requests particular User’s data by available legal means.
3.                  LEGAL BASIS FOR PROCESSING OF PERSONALLY IDENTIFIABLE DATA (Applies only to EEA-based Users)
This section explains what legal basis used my Be-Pass for each particular purpose of processing. For more information on a particular purpose, please refer to Section 2. This section applies only to EEA-based Users.
Be-Pass processes EEA-based User’s personally identifiable data under the following legal bases:
3.1.             to perform our contract with User;
Under this legal basis Be-Pass:
·                Provide Service (in accordance with Terms of Service)
·                Customize User’s experience
·                Manage User account and provide User with customer support
·                Communicate with User regarding User’s use of Service
3.2.            for other legitimate interests, unless those interests are overridden by User’s interests or fundamental rights and freedoms that require protection of personal data;
Be-Pass relies on legitimate interests:
·                to communicate with User regarding User’s use of Service
This includes, for example, sending push notifications reminding payments, delays or newsletters at appropriate times. The legitimate interest Be-Pass rely on for this purpose is interest to encourage User to use Service more often. Be-Pass also takes into account the potential benefits to User of improving their skills or subscribing to a relevant service.
·                to research and analyze User’s use of the Service
Be-Pass legitimate interest for this purpose is interest in improving Service so Be-Pass understands Users’ preferences and is able to provide User with a better experience.
·                to send marketing communications
The legitimate interest Be-Pass relies on for this processing is interest to promote Service in a measured and appropriate way.
·                to personalize advertising
The legitimate interest Be-Pass relies on for this processing is interest to promote Service in a reasonably targeted way.
·                to enforce Terms of Service and to prevent and combat fraud
Legitimate interests for this purpose are enforcing Be-Pass’s legal rights, preventing and addressing fraud and unauthorized use of the Service, non-compliance with our Terms of Service.
3.3.           To comply with legal obligations.
4.                 SHARE OF PERSONALLY IDENTIFIABLE DATA
Be-Pass shares information with third parties that help operate, provide, improve, integrate, customize, support, and market Service. Be-Pass may share some portion of personally identifiable data, such as, for purposes indicated in Section 2 of this Privacy Policy. The types of third parties Be-Pass share information with include, in particular:
4.1.            Service providers
Be-Pass shares personally identifiable data with third parties Be-Pass hires to provide services or perform business functions on Be-Pass’s behalf, based on instructions. Be-Pass share User’s personal information with the following types of service providers:
·                measurement partners
·                cloud storage providers
·                marketing partners (in particular, social media networks, marketing agencies, email delivery services)
·                data analytics providers
4.2.           Law enforcement agencies and other public authorities
Be-Pass may use and disclose personally identifiable data to enforce Terms of Service, to protect Be-Pass rights, privacy, safety, property, and/or that of Be-Pass affiliates, Users or others. Be-Pass may use and disclose personally identifiable data when responding to requests from courts, law enforcement agencies, regulatory agencies, and other public and government authorities, or in other cases provided for by law.
5.                 USER PROFILE
Freelancers, clients, companies, agencies may create a profile, with certain or all information publicly available.
You may have the opportunity to create a profile, which consists of information about you, and may include Personal Information, images, examples of your work, information on work previously performed via the service and outside the service, skills, tests taken, test scores, hourly pay rates and earnings information, feedback/rating information, personal and sensitive information and other information, including your username, email, phone number, ID, age, gender. The information in your Profile may be visible to all Be-Pass Users and the general public subject to the privacy choices you make within your Be-Pass profile. If you choose to make your profile publicly visible, your profile will be visible to the entire Internet, including clients, freelancers, agencies, companies, visitors, and search engines such as Google and Bing, and may appear on Be-Pass partners' sites. You may edit certain information in your profile via your account. clients and agencies of associated individual users or companies may also have the opportunity to create an organization Profile. If, in any case, you believe that an unauthorized profile has been created about you, you can request for it to be removed by contacting us at bepassfeedback@gmail.com.
5.1. Identity Verification
We place a premium on trust in our Service, so we may take steps to verify your identity.
Before a Freelancer or client or agency or company can complete registration on the Service, or at any time thereafter, we may request or re-request identity verification. Without limiting the manner in which we request identity verification, we may require Freelancers to participate in a video call after submitting their government issued ID to enable us to confirm that the Freelancer is indeed the individual in the ID. We may record such video calls and take screenshots of the user during the call. Be-Pass may use the information obtained from Identity Verification for purposes of verifying your identity, enforcing our Terms of Service and other agreements, and preventing fraud.
5.2. Messaging
Freelancers, Companies, Agencies, and Clients may communicate with each other through the Service. For example, Freelancers, Companies, Agencies, and Clients may wish to discuss Client needs and Freelancer work proposals. If you communicate with an Agency or Client, that Agency or Client will also be a “data controller” with respect to such communications.
5.3. Community Forums
We may offer public forums or blogs. If you participate, your comments and questions will be publicly displayed.
The Service may provide you the opportunity to participate and post content publicly in forums, on blogs, through interactive features on Be-Pass and through other communication functionality (“Community Forums”). You may choose, through such features or otherwise, to submit or post questions, comments, or other content (collectively, “User Forum Content”). Please note that certain information, such as your name and Profile may be publicly displayed on the Service along with your User Forum Content. Please note that your use of Community Forums is subject to the Be-Pass Forum Rules and our Terms of Service.
Note that anything you post to a Community Forum is public — others will have access to your User Forum Content and may use it or share it with third parties. If you choose to voluntarily disclose Personal Information in your User Forum Content or use Community Forums to link to your Profile, that information will be considered public information and the protections of this Privacy Policy will not apply.
To request removal of your personal information from our blog or community forum, contact us at bepassfeedback@gmail.com. In some cases, we may not be able to remove your Personal Information, in which case we will let you know if we are unable to do so and why.
5.4. Testimonials
We display personal testimonials of satisfied customers on our Service, in addition to other endorsements. With your consent we may post your testimonial along with your name. If you wish to update or delete your testimonial, you can contact us at bepassfeedback@gmail.com.
5.5. Work Listings Through the Service
If you choose to post a work listing via the Service as a Client, the contents of such listing will be viewable publicly. Work listings include information such as budget, location, history of work listing(s) by the Client, the names of other Freelancers performing work for the Client, Client feedback and rating information and timing of project performance.
5.6. Feedback
We collect public and private feedback from Be-Pass users about their experience with other Be-Pass users of our service. Please note that any public feedback that you provide via the service about your experience with other Be-Pass users of our service or that is provided about you by other users is publicly viewable via the service. on some occasions, we may remove feedback pursuant to the relevant provisions of our Terms of Service, including the Terms of Use. Any private feedback that you provide via the service about your experience with other Be-Pass users of our service or that is provided about you by other users will not be publicly viewable via the service.
We also collect feedback from users about our service. We use this information to respond to your inquiries, improve the service and how our Site functions and develop new features, products, make improvements and performance.
6.                  EXERSICING OF PRIVACY RIGHTS
6.1            To be in control of personal data, User have the following rights:
Accessing / reviewing / updating / correcting personally identifiable information. User may review, edit, or change the personal data that the one had previously provided to Be-Pass in the profile section.
Deleting your personal data. User can request erasure of personally identifiable data by sending an email at bepassfeedback@gmail.com.
When User requested deletion of personally identifiable data, Be-Pass will use reasonable efforts to honor such request. Any request will be answered within 1 month as of its filing. In some cases, Be-Pass may be legally required to keep some portion of the personally identifiable data for a certain time. In such event, Be-Pass will fulfill deletion request after obligations completed.
6.1.1          Additional information for EEA-based Users
6.1.2        Users who based in the EEA have the following rights in addition to the above:
Right to rectification. User has the right to request to rectify, without undue delay, any incorrect data pertaining to the respective User.
Right to limitation of processing. User can limit the use of personally identifiable data collected.
Right of access. User may request a copy of personal data collected during use of the Be-Pass at bepassfeedback@gmail.com.
Objecting to or restricting the use of personal identifiable data. User can ask to stop using all or some portion of personal identifiable data or limit use thereof by requesting its erasure as described above or sending a request at bepassfeedback@gmail.com.
The right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. Users have the right to lodge a complaint with a competent data protection supervisory authority, in particular in the EU Member State where User reside, work or where the alleged infringement has taken place.
The right to data portability. User can receive personal identifiable data in a machine-readable format by sending a respective request at bepassfeedback@gmail.com.
6.1.3        Exercise the rights
To exercise their right to access User have the right to request from the Be-Pass at any time:
-                Confirmation as to whether data related to them is processed by the Be-Pass, the purpose of the processing, the data category, and recipients of such data or the categories of recipients’ data is disclosed to;
-                Information as to the logic of any automated processing of personally identifiable data pertaining to natural persons, at least in the case of automated decisions under the provisions of the GDPR.
Upon request, Be-Pass provides the information free of charge. However, Be-Pass may charge a reasonable fee if request is clearly unfounded, repetitive or excessive. Alternatively, Be-Pass may refuse to comply with User’s request in these circumstances.
The filing of the request is free of charge.
Upon the filing of a request by an authorized person, the notarised power of attorney must be attached to the request.
In case of death of the natural person, his / her rights are exercised by his / her heirs and the certificate of heirs shall be attached to the request. The heritage should be confirmed by a respective certificate, issued in the dead person’s jurisdiction.
Be-Pass shall review and pronounce the request within 1 month of its filing. This period may be extended by an additional two months, if necessary, for example, if User request is especially complex or User has made multiple requests. The Be-Pass shall inform the User as to any such extension within 1 month of receipt of the request, stating the reasons for the delay. When the User files a request by electronic means, the information is provided electronically, if possible, unless the User has requested otherwise.
Be-Pass provides an answer to the requesting person taking into account their preferred form for the provision of the information (orally or in writing - as a hard copy of electronically).
Where data do not exist or their provision is forbidden by law, access of the requesting party to such data is refused.
If the requesting party is not satisfied with the response received and / or believes that their rights related to personally identifiable data protection were violated, they are entitled to exercise their right to defense.
7.       AGE LIMITATION
Be-Pass does not knowingly process personal data from persons under 18 years of age. If you learn that anyone younger than 18 years old has provided us with personal data, please contact us at bepassfeedback@gmail.com
8.     INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS
Be-Pass may transfer and maintain on servers or databases some of User’s personally identifiable data outside the European Economic Area (EEA) including in Israel and the United States of America.
The countries to which User’s personally identifiable data is transferred may not have the same data protection laws as User’s jurisdiction. Be-Pass takes reasonable cyber security measures and/or put in place the Standard Contractual Clauses (e.g. Model Clauses, Data Processing Agreement/Addendum) to ensure adequate protection of Personally identifiable data.
9.       CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
We may modify this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we decide to make material changes to this Privacy Policy, you will be notified through our Service or by other available means and will have an opportunity to review the revised Privacy Policy. By continuing to access or use the Service after those changes become effective, you agree to be bound by the revised Privacy Policy.
10.   SECURITY MEASURES
Be-Pass takes technical, organizational, and legal measures, including, where suitable, encryption, to ensure that personally identifiable data are protected from unauthorized or accidental access, deletion, modification, blocking, copying, and dissemination.
 
11.     CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS
California’s Shine the Light law gives California residents the right to ask companies once a year what personal information they share with third parties for those third parties direct marketing purposes. Learn more about what is considered to be personal information under the statute.
If User is a California resident, Be-Pass will provide the requested information to respective User email address. To obtain this information from lease User may send an email message to bepassfeedback@gmail.com which includes “Request for California Privacy Information” on the subject line and state of residence.
Notice: not all information sharing is covered by the “Shine the Light” requirements and only information on covered sharing will be included in the response.
12.   DATA RETENTION
Be-Pass will store Personally identifiable data for as long as it is reasonably necessary for achieving the purposes set forth in this Privacy Policy and Terms of Service, which includes (but is not limited to) the period during which User has an account. Be-Pass will also retain and use personally identifiable data as necessary to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements.
13.   DATA CONTROLLER
SMART WORKOUT APP LTD, a company registered in the State of Israel (with a registered office at Hod-Hasharon, Moshe Sharet 27) will be the controller of User’s personally identifiable data. For any questions concerning account or personally identifiable data please contact us at bepassfeedback@gmail.com.
The SMART WORKOUT APP LTD has registered a database with the Israeli Database Registrar.
14.   WEBSITE COOKIES
 
The Be-Pass website (Website) uses cookies and similar technologies. Cookies are usually a string of numbers and/or letters that a website transfers to your hard drive. Similar technologies include pixel tags and web storage and other technologies. All these things are called cookies in this section. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to.
The Website uses the following types of cookies:

Strictly necessary cookies. These cookies are essential to enable the user to navigate around the Website securely.
Functionality cookies
These cookies enhance the functionality of the Website by storing user preferences.
Performance cookies - These cookies improve the performance of the Website. For instance, they help pages load quicker.
Analytics cookies. Website uses third party analytics services such as Google Analytics and others. Your IP address and other information will be collected by automated means to evaluate use of the website, compile reports on website activity, identify user patterns and provide related services. In addition, authentication and tracking logs will be used to compile user statistics.
When you are using our website you agree to our use of cookies.
Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but if you prefer, you can change your browser to prevent that, or opt-out as explained below. You may not be able to take full advantage of our platforms or use certain functions if you disable cookies.

15. EUROPEAN UNION PERSONAL DATA PROTECTION – ADDITIONAL PRECISIONS

The personal data collected as part of the Terms of Service, Privacy policy and the provision of the Service may be subject to automated processing by the company, acting as data controller, for the purposes of carrying out the Service, invoicing and collection.
The legal basis for this processing is the performance of these Agreements and compliance with the legal obligations of the Company and the User.
The data collected are kept for the time necessary to carry out the purposes of the processing.

The Company and the User are aware that their services include the processing of confidential data, in particular any personal data within the meaning of the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the law of the Member State of residence of the User, including their implementing provisions. They therefore undertake to destroy any copy of such data that they may hold as soon as the reason for their transmission no longer exists.
They certify that such data will not be stored in machines located outside its business premises.
The Company and the User undertake to perform their services in accordance with the requirements of the law of the Member State of residence of the User and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).

